# DuckDB-wasm File Loading Issue

The problem is that DuckDB-wasm runs in a **browser environment without direct file system access**. It can't read `'test.parquet'` from your local disk using a relative path.

## Solutions

### Option 1: Load from HTTP URL (Simplest)

If your parquet file is served from a server:

```typescript
async makeConnection() {
  const JSDELIVR_BUNDLES = duckdb.getJsDelivrBundles();
  const bundle = await duckdb.selectBundle(JSDELIVR_BUNDLES);

  const worker_url = URL.createObjectURL(
    new Blob([`importScripts("${bundle.mainWorker}");`], {
      type: 'text/javascript',
    })
  );

  const worker = new Worker(worker_url);
  const logger = new duckdb.ConsoleLogger();
  const db = new duckdb.AsyncDuckDB(logger, worker);
  await db.instantiate(bundle.mainModule, bundle.pthreadWorker);

  const conn = await db.connect();
  // Load from HTTP URL
  const results = await conn.query(`SELECT * FROM read_parquet('http://localhost:3000/test.parquet')`);
  console.log(results);
}
```

### Option 2: File Upload Handler (Recommended for UX)

Allow users to upload a parquet file:

```typescript
async makeConnection() {
  const JSDELIVR_BUNDLES = duckdb.getJsDelivrBundles();
  const bundle = await duckdb.selectBundle(JSDELIVR_BUNDLES);

  const worker_url = URL.createObjectURL(
    new Blob([`importScripts("${bundle.mainWorker}");`], {
      type: 'text/javascript',
    })
  );

  const worker = new Worker(worker_url);
  const logger = new duckdb.ConsoleLogger();
  const db = new duckdb.AsyncDuckDB(logger, worker);
  await db.instantiate(bundle.mainModule, bundle.pthreadWorker);

  this.db = db;
  this.conn = await db.connect();
}

async loadParquetFile(file: File) {
  const buffer = await file.arrayBuffer();
  await this.db.registerFileBuffer(file.name, new Uint8Array(buffer));
  const results = await this.conn.query(`SELECT * FROM read_parquet('${file.name}')`);
  console.log(results);
  return results;
}
```

**In your component:**

```html
<input type="file" accept=".parquet" (change)="onFileSelected($event)" />
```

```typescript
onFileSelected(event: Event) {
  const file = (event.target as HTMLInputElement).files?.[0];
  if (file) {
    this.duckdbService.loadParquetFile(file);
  }
}
```

### Option 3: Using registerFileURL

```typescript
